.TH man 1 "04 August 2022, Holberton School Uruguay" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
$cisfun [name of the command][arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Holbie-made UNIX command line interpreter
.SH COMPLILING
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
This command interpreter is based on te UNIX shell command line interpreter made by Ken Thompson.
			Our version allows execution of commands that had to be writen in the standart input.
.SH USAGE
This program should be used in a interactive mode, that will show "$cisfun " and the user can write commands and that will be execute. This process is being repeat until the user itself stop it typing "exit" or Ctrl + D. Otherwise, it can be usedin the non interactive mode, where the user can write an output of a command line like an input to the ./hsh program with an |.
.SH AUTHORS
Santiago Alves
Romina Benitez
